                <body xml:id="ch1.sc2.0016">                        
                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.—<name type="person" key="133">Sergeant Richard M. Porter</name>, <name type="organization" key="164">37th Massachusetts
                                                Volunteers</name>, aged 28 years, received a
                                        contusion of the scalp, in <date type="injury" when="1864-07">July, 1864</date>. He was admitted
                                        into <name type="hospital" key="218">Augur Hospital</name>,
                                        and, on <date type="transfer" when="1864-08-02">August
                                                2d</date>, he was transferred to the <name type="hospital" key="189">3d Division
                                                        Hospital</name>, at <name type="place">Alexandria</name>, with symptoms of
                                        incipient cerebritis.  He died, <date type="death" when="1864-08-28">August 28th, 1864</date>.   <name type="person" key="134">Surgeon E. Bentley</name>,
                                                <name type="organization" key="132">U. S. V.</name>,
                                        records the case. </p>                        
